<% include head.ejs %>
  <body>
<% include header.ejs %>
    <div id="index-banner" class="parallax-container">
      <div class="section no-pad-bot">
        <div class="container">
          <br><br>
          <h1 class="header center teal-text text-lighten-2"><%= title %></h1>
          <div class="row center">
            <h5 class="header col s12 light" style="color:white">The Ringed Planet</h5>
          </div>
          <br>
          <br>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="parallax"><img src="http://images-assets.nasa.gov/image/PIA12513/PIA12513~orig.jpg" alt="<%= title %> img 1" style="width:100%"></div>
    </div>
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section">
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col s12 center">
            <h3><i class="mdi-content-send brown-text"></i></h3>
            <h4>Saturn</h4>
            <p class="flow-text left-align light">Saturn is the sixth planet from the Sun and the second-largest in the Solar System, after Jupiter. It is a gas giant with an average radius about nine times that of Earth.  Saturn's interior is probably composed of a core of iron–nickel and rock (silicon and oxygen compounds). This core is surrounded by a deep layer of metallic hydrogen, an intermediate layer of liquid hydrogen and liquid helium, and finally a gaseous outer layer.  Saturn has a pale yellow hue due to ammonia crystals in its upper atmosphere.
<br>
<br>
Saturn has a prominent ring system that consists of nine continuous main rings and three discontinuous arcs and that is composed mostly of ice particles with a smaller amount of rocky debris and dust. Sixty-two moons are known to orbit Saturn, of which fifty-three are officially named. This does not include the hundreds of moonlets comprising the rings. Titan, Saturn's largest moon, and the second-largest in the Solar System, is larger than the planet Mercury, although less massive, and is the only moon in the Solar System to have a substantial atmosphere.
<div>Source: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Saturn</div>
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="parallax-container valign-wrapper">
      <div class="section no-pad-bot">
        <div class="container">
          <h4 style="color:white"> <%= title %>: Stats</h4>
          <p><i>The density of Saturn is the lowest of any planet in the Solar System.</i></p>
          <p>At only <%= planet.density %> times the density of Earth, Saturn would actually float on water!.</p>
          <br>
          <p><i>(Assuming you could find a pool big enough to fit the second largest planet in the Solar System!).</i></p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="parallax"><img src="https://www.nasa.gov/images/content/365640main_PIA11141_full.jpg" alt="<%= title %> img 2" style="width:100%"></div>
    </div>

    <div class="container">
      <div class="section">
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col s12 m6">
            <p class="flow-text left-align light">
              Saturn orbits 1427 million kilometers from the Sun.
              <br>
              At our Manhattan scale, Saturn is 4.71 kilometers away from The Sphere.
              <br>
              In our journey across Manhattan, this puts us on Broadway at East 22nd Street, just south of the Flatiron Building.
              <br>
              Saturn would be about 39.5cm in size at this scale.
              <br>
          </div>
          <div class="col s12 m6 materialboxed" data-caption="Relative orbit of Saturn from The Sphere">

              <img  src="/images/Saturn_orbit.png" alt="Raduis of <%= title %>'s orbit at scale" style="width:100%">

          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

      <div style="position:relative;height:400px;width:80%;margin:0 auto">

      <iframe width="100%" height="400"
        src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed/v1/streetview?key=<%= process.env.GOOGLE_KEY %>&location=40.7406074,-73.9893891&heading=45&pitch=5&fov=100">
      </iframe>

      <div style="width:900px;height:400px;z-index:2;position:absolute;top:0px">
        <a-scene embedded style="left:250;height:300;width:400">
          <a-sphere position="0 1.8 -1" radius=".03" color="#e58c5d"></a-sphere>
        </a-scene>
      </div>

    </div>

    <div class="container section no-pad-bot">
      <p style="text-align:center">Saturn, 39cm in size, orbits above Broadway near the Flatiron Building. (Use arrow keys / mouse to pan / zoom)</p>
    </div>

    <div class="container">
      <div class="section">
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col s12 center">
            <p class="flow-text light">Next, the ice giants.
            </p>
            <div class="row center">
              <a href="/uranus" class="btn-large waves-effect waves-light teal lighten-1">Next: URANUS</a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <footer class="page-footer teal">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col s12">
            <h5 class="white-text">Sources</h5>
            <p class="grey-text text-lighten-4">"A New Yorker's Guide to the Solar System" was conceived as a showcase for web technologies explored under the Web Development Immersive at General Assembly NYC in February 2017. Several of these are linked here.</p>
            <p class="grey-text text-lighten-4">All images from NASA's Jet Propulsion Laboratory and Google fair use searches.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="footer-copyright">
        <div class="container">
          <p>Developed by <a class="brown-text text-lighten-3" href="https://github.com/franklinbrooks">Franklin Brooks</a>. Created with
            <span class="heart">♥
            </span> at
            <span><a  class="brown-text text-lighten-3" href="http://www.generalassemb.ly">GA</a>
            </span>
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </footer>
    <!--  Scripts-->
    <script src="https://code.jquery.com/jquery-2.1.4.min.js"></script>
    <script src="http://www.materializecss.com/bin/materialize.js"></script>
    <script src="http://www.materializecss.com/js/init.js"></script>
    <script src="https://darkskyapp.github.io/skycons/skycons.js"></script>
  </body>
</html>
